data.meta_description: Justin Timberlake heads out on 'The Man of the Woods' tour! Justin Timberlake at the Golden 1 Center Sacramento, CA. Finished Feb 24, 2019.  Buy tickets online now or find out more with Sacramento Theater
data.text:
Justin Timberlake Is Bringing Sexy Back!

Admit it; you loved Justin Timberlake as a member of pop-powerhouse NSYNC. Now, as a solo performer, Justin Timberlake has hit it big with songs like Cry Me a River, Like I Love You, Mirrors and many more! The prince of pop has announced his first tour since 2019's The Man of The Woods tour! Following the launch of his upcoming album, 'Everything I Thought It Was,' on March 15, the vocal sensation will embark on the Forget Tomorrow world tour.

Dropping a Filthy tour

Rock your body to all of the hits you know and love! The epic celebration of one of the most celebrated voices in pop will include tracks from his highly-anticipated new album, including the lead single 'Selfish'. With a never-ending range of talent, a Timberlake tour is the ultimate experience - and we're not about the 20/20 Experience!

The North American leg of his Forget Tomorrow world tour will open April 29 in Canada at Vancouver's Rogers Arena and conclude July 9 at in Kentucky at Lexington's Rupp Arena.
